NAME
-----
xe-pif-reconfigure-ipv6 - Configure PIF IPv6 addressing

SYNOPSIS
--------
*xe pif-reconfigure-ipv6*	mode=[ autoconf | dhcp | none ]	uuid=<PIF UUID>

*xe pif-reconfigure-ipv6*	mode=static uuid=<PIF UUID> IPV6=<IPv6 ADDRESS> [ gateway=<GATEWAY ADDRESS> ] [ DNS=<NAME SERVER> ]

DESCRIPTION
-----------
*xe pif-reconfigure-ipv6* configures IPv6 address settings for a specific PIF. Address changes are applied immediately upon command excution.

The IPv6 ADDRESS must be followed by a slash and a decimal number which encodes the network prefix length.

REQUIRED PARAMETERS
-------------------
*mode*::
	Addressing mode for the PIF: mode=*[ dhcp | static | autoconf | none ]*
*uuid*::
	PIF UUID - Use *xe pif-list* to obtain PIF interface UUIDs
*IPv6*::
	PIF IPv6 address. Address is only required for static mode.

OPTIONAL PARAMETERS
-------------------
*DNS*::
	Name server addresses - Use a comma to seperate multiple name servers 
*gateway*::
	Gateway address
	
EXAMPLES
--------
To set dhcp mode:

- *xe pif-reconfigure-ipv6* mode="dhcp" uuid=<PIF UUID>

To set the address mode to static with a gateway address and one DNS server:

- *xe pif-reconfigure-ipv6* mode="static" uuid=<PIF UUID> IPv6=<IPV6 ADDRESS> gateway=<GATEWAY ADDRESS> DNS=<NAME SERVER>

